properties.story: Sandwiched between Grand Boulevard and the Villages, Islandview is a majority-Black neighborhood that is home to lots of multi-generational families. The neighborhood is home to several churches and block clubs. Housing stock here is often more than 100 years old and can be high-end in places. Islandview has been targeted for development by the city and is gentrifying even as seniors in the neighborhood struggle to maintain their homes.

properties.story:
Islandview doesn't quite know what it is. It is between downtown, and Indian Village. The majority of Islandview is empty warehouses, but has a major advantage with the riverwalk, and proximity to Belle Isle. 

By including the riverwalk in front of Jefferson, and Gabriel Ricahrd Park, Islandview has the potential to draw many more residences, unique warehouse businesses, coffee shops, event spaces, and public transportation. It is a perfect spot to develop between downtown, and historic Indian Village to eliminate a "dead" feel on Jefferson between those two communities.
There's a great storymap of the History of Woodbridge Housing linked on this page: www.woodbridgendc.org/neighborhood-history
